input_str: Family ties … the author as a baby with his parents, Rhonda and Michael. Enmore was a rough neighbourhood back then. Drug and alcohol abuse was common, and I'd often hear huge fights as I lay awake at night. I remember being scared a lot. I slept with an axe next to my bed after being threatened for not paying enough protection money to a local gang. Mum loved trains, and it's something I inherited from her.
